cSetAttribute.name: cSetAttribute
cSetAttribute.desc: This is the ID of the `Set Attribute` effect of the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This sets the HP of unit 74 (militia) to 100 (the value). Alternatively, any of the [Unit Attribute Constants](./#7-effectamount-unit-attribute "Jump to: Unit Attribute Constants") may be used to modify the corresponding unit property

cModResource.name: cModResource
cModResource.desc: This is the ID of the `Modify Resource` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This adds 100 to the current food amount. Alternatively, `cAttributeSet` may be used to set the food amount to 100. Also, see the [Resource](./#9-resource "Jump to: Constant Reference > Resource")

cEnableObject.name: cEnableObject
cEnableObject.desc: This is the ID of the `Enable (or disable) Object` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This disables the unit 74 (militia). Alternatively, `cAttributeEnable` may be used to enable an object instead

cUpgradeUnit.name: cUpgradeUnit
cUpgradeUnit.desc: This is the ID of the `Upgrade Unit` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This copies all units attributes except ID and available from unit 75 (man at arms) to 74 (militia)

cAddAttribute.name: cAddAttribute
cAddAttribute.desc: This is the ID of the `Add Attribute` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This adds 100 (the value) to the attribute 0 (HP) of unit 74 (militia)

cMulAttribute.name: cMulAttribute
cMulAttribute.desc: This is the ID of the `Multiply Attribute` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This multiplies the attribute 0 (HP) of unit 74 (militia) by 100 (the value)

cMulResource.name: cMulResource
cMulResource.desc: This is the ID of the `Multiply Resource` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.explanation: This multiplies the food amount by 10 (the value)

cSpawnUnit.name: cSpawnUnit
cSpawnUnit.desc: This is the ID of the `Spawn Unit` effect for the xsEffectAmount function

usage.syntax:
xsEffectAmount(cModResource, cAttributeSpawnCap, cAttributeSet, numBuildings);
 xsEffectAmount(cSpawnUnit, unitID, buildingID, numUnits)
usage.explanation: This will spawn 5 villagers (83) from each town centre (109), for a maximum of 2 town centres. Note that setting the `cAttributeCap` resource to a non 0 value is required for using this effect. If you prefer spawning the units garrisoned set resource `cAttributeSpawnStayInside` to 1.
